      "content": "# Endpoint Documentation: GET /user\n\n## Overview\nThis endpoint provides a complete profile snapshot for the currently authenticated user. It is fundamental for session validation and personalization across the CloudScale platform.\n\n## Request Details\n### Path Parameters\nNone.\n\n### Query Parameters\nNone.\n\n## Authentication and Authorization\n### Security Requirements\nAccess to this endpoint strictly requires a valid Bearer Token provided in the `Authorization` header. Unauthorized requests will receive a 401 response.\n\n## Response Structure\n### Success Response (200 OK)\nThe response body is a JSON object containing the user's core attributes.\n\n#### Response Body Schema\n| Field | Type | Description | Constraints |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `id` | string | The immutable, unique identifier assigned to the user. | Required |\n| `username` | string | The display name chosen by the user. | Required |\n| `email` | string | The verified contact email address. | Required |\n\n## Error Handling\n### Detailed Error Codes\n*   **401 Unauthorized:** The provided token is missing, expired, or malformed.\n*   **500 Internal",
      "source": "target",
